headline: New CA Gas Price Spike Fault of Newsom Energy Commission's Oversight Failure, Legislative Hearings Warranted, Says Consumer Watchdog
summary: Consumer Watchdog said today that the California Energy Commission (CEC) was not using the powers the legislature granted several years ago to stem a current gasoline price spike.

headline: Reasons Why PSX's Midstream Portfolio Offsets Elevated Crude Prices
summary: Phillips 66 stands to gain as the EIA predicts falling crude prices through 2027, while its expanding midstream arm generates steady, fee-based cash flows.

headline: USA Compression Q4 Earnings Match Estimates, Revenues Rise Y/Y
summary: USAC expects adjusted EBITDA of $770-$800 million and distributable cash flow between $480 million and $510 million for 2026.
